            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-17T09:31:12+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-17T09:31:12+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-17T00:01:12Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-17T00:01:12Z">
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system south of the Bight extends a ridge over SA. The high will move east during today and Saturday ahead of a weakening trough that is expected to brush the west and south on the weekend. The high is forecast to be over the Tasman Sea by Monday, extending a ridge over South Australia through until Tuesday.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
